# WANTED engine — ESP-IDF component glue. Host-edge only: the engine's own
# Kconfig tree (repository root) is read standalone, and any CONFIG_WANTED_*
# declared here would shadow the engine's value.
#
# What belongs here is what crosses into ESP-IDF's own symbols — the engine
# tree must never reference a host symbol because kconfiglib resolves an
# unknown one to n without stopping.

menu "WANTED engine"

config WANTED_ESP_TLS
    bool "TLS secure sockets (mbedTLS)"
    default n
    select MBEDTLS_TLS_ENABLED
    help
        Backs the engine's secure socket types (tcps://, udps://) with the
        mbedTLS ESP-IDF ships, and builds the engine with SECURE_SOCKETS=1.
        Mirrors the NuttX app's SYSTEM_WANTED_TLS — the engine says "I want
        TLS" through its socket driver, each host says "and here is the stack"
        through its own symbol. Without this the engine still builds; secure
        socket entries are rejected when a wapp launches.

endmenu
